samplenarrat: Samples are all volume weighted means from four depths throughout the watercolumn. Periodn is the number of sampling events used in the winter (Jan-May) or summer stratified (July-Aug) period that contribute to the mean and CV computations. Iceon seasons for 1984-1988, 1992-1993, 1995, and 2000-2001 are set to the winter range noted here - exact day not provided. Note that for iceon 2000 this does conflict with periodn = 1.
icenarrat: Sierra lake ice is not solid ice as found in other lakes. It is a series of ice lenses covered and pushed into the lake by the weight of accumulating snow until it forms a solidish mass. The values I've given here are general seaosnal averages as we don't have consistent measurements through time. Ice depth average: 200 cm, snow depth average: 100 cm
waterchemnarrat: Water samples for dissolved nutrient analyses (nitrate, total dissolved nitrogen [TDN], and total dissolved phosphorus [TDP]) were filtered with a 1.0-mm polycarbonate filter in the field and stored refrigerated in 125-ml polyethylene bottles until analyzed. TDN, TDP were determined by the Valderrama (1981) digestion method. Nitrate and phosphate in the digests were measured on a Latchet autoanalyzer or manually using the cadmium reduction and phosphomolybdate methods, respectively (Strickland and Parsons 1972). DOC samples were acidified to remove inorganic carbon and analyzed on a Shimadzu TOC analyzer. Chla was extracted in 90% acetone and analyzed on a Turner 10 AU Fluorimeter.

waterchemnarrat: Water samples for dissolved nutrient analyses (nitrate, total dissolved nitrogen [TDN], and total dissolved phosphorus [TDP]) were filtered with a 1.0-mm polycarbonate filter in the field and stored refrigerated in 125-ml polyethylene bottles until analyzed. TDN, TDP were determined by the Valderrama (1981) digestion method. Nitrate and phosphate in the digests were measured on a Latchet autoanalyzer or manually using the cadmium reduction and phosphomolybdate methods, respectively (Strickland and Parsons 1972). DOC samples were acidified to remove inorganic carbon and analyzed on a Shimadzu TOC analyzer. Chla was extracted in 90% acetone and analyzed on a Turner 10 AU Fluorimeter.

samplenarrat: Samples are all volume weighted means from four depths throughout the watercolumn. Periodn is the number of sampling events used in the winter (Jan-May) or summer stratified (July-Aug) period that contribute to the mean and CV computations. Iceon seasons for 1984-1988, 1992-1993, 1995, and 2000-2001 are set to the winter range noted here - exact day not provided. Note that for iceon 2000 this does conflict with periodn = 1.

Periodn is the number of sampling events used in the winter (Jan-May) or summer stratified (July-Aug) period that contribute to the mean and CV computations. Iceon seasons for 1984-1988, 1992-1993, 1995, and 2000-2001 are set to the winter range noted here - exact day not provided. Note that for iceon 2000 this does conflict with periodn = 1.
icenarrat: Sierra lake ice is not solid ice as found in other lakes. It is a series of ice lenses covered and pushed into the lake by the weight of accumulating snow until it forms a solidish mass. The values I've given here are general seaosnal averages as we don't have consistent measurements through time. Ice depth average: 200 cm, snow depth average: 100 cm
waterchemnarrat: Water samples for dissolved nutrient analyses (nitrate, total dissolved nitrogen [TDN], and total dissolved phosphorus [TDP]) were filtered with a 1.0-mm polycarbonate filter in the field and stored refrigerated in 125-ml polyethylene bottles until analyzed. DOC samples were acidified to remove inorganic carbon and analyzed on a Shimadzu TOC analyzer. Chla was extracted in 90% acetone and analyzed on a Turner 10 AU Fluorimeter.

samplenarrat: This reservoir experienced considerable variability throughout the iceoff period during a hypolimnetic oxygenation experiment; however, the oxygenation did not alter thermal stratification and we thus only included our epilimnetic (subsurface) samples for both iceon and iceoff periods. We are confident that the epilimnion was not affected by oxygenation (as discussed in more detail by Gerling et al. 2014 Water Research)
waterchemnarrat: Chlorophyll a concentrations were converted from cell count data; we used the size measurements of the cells to calculate biovolume/biomass. We assumed that chlorophyll a was 0.505% wet weight of the phytoplankton, following Kasprzaka et al. 2008 Limnologica.
phytomethod: Phytoplankton were collected with a 1 L whole-water sub-surface grab sample and preserved with Lugol's solution.  Subsamples were counted on an upright light microscope using Palmer-Maloney or Sedgwick-Rafter chambers

waterchemnarrat: TP and TDP (<0.2um) were analyzed colourimetrically (Parsons et al. 1984); TN and nitrate were analyzed via second derivative spectroscopy (Bachmann and Canfield, 1996; Crumpton et al., 1992) and ammonium was analyzed by the phenol method (Stainton et al. 1977). Our TDN is only nitrate+ammonium, and doesn't include dissolved organic N. Chla was corrected for pheophytin on GFF filters (0.7 um pore size) and analyzed according to Bergmann and Peters (1980) and Webb et al. (1992) using ethanol as a solvent
profiles: yes; though we only have one additional bottom-water depth for each sample
phytopprnarrat: Gross phytoplankton productivity was derived from  relative light curve P-E parameters measured on a Water-PAM fluorometerusing the R package 'phytotools' that is based on the primary production model described by Fee (1990), assuming quantum yield of O2 evolution is 0.25
phytomethod: Whole water samples collected with a peristaltic pump from defined depths, perserved with lugols

samplenarrat: Sampling conducted from icebreaker USCGC NEAH BAY from water cleared of ice by the vessel
icenarrat: 9/10 ice coverage in Feb with 1-3 inch plate ice
waterchemnarrat: Nutrients analyzed by National Center for Water Quality Research (Heidelberg University, Tiffin, OH, USA) using standardized techniques (EPA 1979). Chlorophyll measured flourometrically on pigment extracted in 90% acetone from samples collected on 0.2 micron PCTE membranes
phytopprnarrat: Photosynthetic rates were measured by tracing the acid-stable uptake of radiolabelled 14C HCO3 in samples incubated simultaneously under 24 different light intensities for 2-3 h using a temperature-controlled photosynthetron
phytomethod: Sampling was as described elsewhere (Twiss et al., 2012, JGLR). A stainless steel sampling bucket was lowered to 1 m and sample collected.

Immediately follow filtration, filters were placed in 90% acetone in the dark for 4 to 24 hr at 4 deg C and then measured fluorometrically following the Welschmeyer (1994) technique. A correction factor of 1.34 was applied to total chlorophyll-a results to reflect an increase in efficiency of extraction  if filters are frozen (-15C) prior to acetone extraction details in Smith D.E. (2011) (masters thesis).

samplenarrat: Since depth of photic zone was not estimated, based on observations in other years we averaged values of physico-chemical variable between 0 and -15 m depth; Phytoplankton was sampled on 4 out of 5 dates.
waterchemnarrat: Chlorophyll-a was analysed spectrophotometrically according to Lorenzen (1967). If desired, we can provide NO3, NH4, SiO2, PO4 concentrations
phytomethod: Phytoplankton samples were collected at different depths over the whole water column with a Ruttner bottle. Samples were fixed with Lugol's solution. Phytoplankton were identified and counted with an inverted microscope according to Utermohl (1958). Densities are reported as volume-weighted average over the whole water column.
zoopmethod: Quantitative zooplankton samples were collected by vertical hauls over the whole water column using a 230 micrometer net. Samples were immediately fixed with buffered formaldehyde.

samplenarrat: Chlorophyll-a was measured on 4 out of 8 dates, while phytoplankton was sampled on 5 out of 8 dates. Benthos was sampled on 3 out of 8 dates

phytopprnarrat: 14C tracer method, light gradient incubator. Incubation temperature was within 2 ?C of in situ, primary production rates were calculated using software developed by Fee (1990) where areal production (Pint, mg-C m-2 d-1) was calculated from surface down to the 1% PAR depth or to the station physical depth, whichever was lesser.
bactprodmethod: simultaneous incorporation of methyl-3H thymidine and 14C-leucine (Chin-Leo and Kirchman 1988) details on this bacterial data available from Quinn, C.J., North, R.L., and Dillon, P.J. 2013. Year-round patterns in bacterial production and biomass in Lake Simcoe, Ontario, Canada: are heterotrophic bacteria a significant contributor to low hypolimnetic oxygen? Inland Waters 3(2): 235-252.
bactcompnarrat: Bacterial abundance, biovolume, and biomass data available derived from epifluorescence microscopy

waterchemnarrat: TP, TDP, nitrate and ammonium (<0.2um) were analyzed colourimetrically (OMOE 2007a, b); Our TDN is only nitrate+nitrite+ammonium, and doesn't include dissolved organic N. Chla was corrected for pheophytin on GFF filters (0.7 um pore size) and analyzed according to Smith et al. 1999 using passive extraction with acetone
profiles: yes; though we only have one additional bottom-water depth for each sample

foodwebnarrat: We have yellow perch FA data from 2013 in Jun, Aug, Oct

phytomethod: Wisconsin net; 20 um mesh; from 2.5 x secchi depth to surface, 2 reps, 11.75 cm mouth diameter; samples not processed

fishnarrat: We have collected yellow perch in fall; plan for selectivity analyses

samplenarrat: Hyper-eutrophic, polymictic system, occassional stratification during windless periods
waterchemnarrat: We have sonde data taken every 0.5 m on pH, DO, conductivity, turbidity, relative units of chl-a and phycocyanin; we also have depth-specific SRP; will have TN/TP and nitrate/nitrite eventually

fishnarrat: Starting to collect yellow perch in winter; plan for selectivity analyses, possibly age and growth

samplenarrat: Water column profiled using CTD at 1 m intervals; water collected at 6 discrete depths on each montly sampling date (2-4 in euphotoc zone). Aggregated samples here were those collected in the estimated photic zone. Iceoff 8m photic depth based on estimate from Lake Ozonia.
waterchemnarrat: Chl-a measured using Welschemeyer (1994) technique; data on anions and cations available.
